Hello I just wanted to say that your security level has a severe problem. I was issued a check from your co. and I held on to it for a couple of months when I did deposit it, there was a stop payment and the quantity of that check was deducted from my checking account. I called to find the reason why this happened and was told that someone called and gave a different address and a second check was issued to this address which is not mine, but no security question was asked from this person, all they gave was my name address and SS# which can be obtained rummaging through the trash, but when I call they always ask for my mothers maiden name which was not requested when this person called to change the address. Now I have an amount deducted on my banking account because of this.

According to this site:  http://www.badfaithinsurance.org/reference/Life/L0455a.htm, premiums and death benefit for the "whole" or "traditional" policy remains the same for the life of the contract.  Is there any way to find out why some whole life policy premiums with New York Life suddenly increasing with not enough explanations.  I think that some life insurance agencies try to increase premiums hoping that policyholders default on their premiums.  This way they could keep whatever premiums have been paid to them.  Can we look at these problems closely.  I do want anyone get taken advantage of unfair practices, such as these, especially our loved ones and the elderly.  Thanks a million!

Thanks to our generous sponsors including New York Life Insurance Company, Brotherton Cadillac Buick GMC, Savers/Value Village, and the Seattle Mariners,  100% of the funds raised that day will benefit children impacted by loss and family addiction.
